'''A Lamusi''' ([[Mongolian language|Mongolian]]: Almas; 2 June 1989 in [[Inner Mongolia]])<ref name=london2012>{{cite web | url = http://www.london2012.com/athlete/a-lamusi-1074544/ | title = Lamusi A | publisher = London2012.com | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20130424182444/http://www.london2012.com/athlete/a-lamusi-1074544/ | archivedate = 24 April 2013}}</ref> is a [[Southern Mongol]] judoka who represented China in the men's 60&nbsp;kg category at the [[2012 Summer Olympics]], he was [[Judo at the 2012 Summer Olympics – Men's 60 kg|defeated]] in the second round by [[Javier Guédez]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.judoinside.com/judoka/view/62489/|title=A. Lamusi (China) - Judo stats and info|publisher=JudoInside.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=A Lamusi Olympic Profile|url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/a/a-lamusi-1.html|website=sports-reference.com|publisher=Sports Reference LLC|accessdate=29 November 2015}}</ref>

